## Feature — configurable edit-lock lease TTL in Settings › Global

### Context

The DRAFT single-editor lease TTL was only settable via the
`ONTOBRICKS_EDIT_LOCK_TTL_S` env var (default 600s = 10 min), which requires a
redeploy to change. Requested: expose it as a runtime, admin-editable setting in
**Settings › Global**, defaulting to 10 min. Reuses the existing global-config
(`GlobalConfigService`) + `registry_cache_ttl` UI pattern. Precedence is now
**Settings › Global** value → `ONTOBRICKS_EDIT_LOCK_TTL_S` env → built-in
default (600s). `0` still disables the lease (hold-until-close).

### Changes

1. `src/back/objects/session/GlobalConfigService.py`
   - Added `get_edit_lock_ttl_s(...)` (returns the stored seconds or `None` when
     unset — deliberately **absent from `_empty()`** so an unconfigured / failed
     load yields the sentinel and the caller falls through to env/default) and
     `set_edit_lock_ttl_s(...)` (persists `edit_lock_ttl_s`, clamps `>= 0`).
